To change the color of the jokes displayed on your webpage to red using CSS, you can modify the `<style>` section in your HTML document. Here’s how you can do it:

1. Locate the `<style>` section in your HTML file, typically within the `<head>` section.
2. Add a CSS rule that targets the `#jokeDisplay` element, which is where your jokes are displayed.
3. Set the `color` property to `red`.

Here's the modified HTML with the added CSS rule:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Random Joke Generator</title>
<style>
    body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
    }
    .container {
        margin-top: 50px;
    }
    #jokeDisplay {
        color: red; /* Set the color of the joke text to red */
    }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
    <h1>Random Joke Generator</h1>
    <button onclick="showRandomJoke()">Get Joke</button>
    <p id="jokeDisplay"></p>
</div>

<script>
    // Array of jokes
    var jokes = [
        "Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts.",
        "What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta.",
        "Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field.",
        "I told my wife she should embrace her mistakes. She gave me a hug."
    ];

    function showRandomJoke() {
        // Generate a random index
        var randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);

        // Display the random joke
        document.getElementById('jokeDisplay').innerText = jokes[randomIndex];
    }
</script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

- **CSS Rule**: 
  - Added `#jokeDisplay { color: red; }` inside the `<style>` section.
  - `#jokeDisplay` targets the `<p>` element with `id="jokeDisplay"`.
  - `color: red;` sets the text color of the jokes to red.

Now, when you open this HTML file in a web browser and click the "Get Joke" button, the randomly selected joke will be displayed in red color. This simple CSS rule modifies the appearance of the text without changing any other styling of the webpage. Adjust as needed to achieve the desired visual effect for your random joke generator.

